BLITZ 6-MAX PREFLOP STRATEGY (2NL-10NL)

SUIT CHECK: Same suit = suited (s). Different = offsuit (o).

BLITZ POOL TRUTHS
- Blinds fold 65%+ to steals → steal wide from BTN/CO
- 3-bets are 90% value → fold marginal hands
- Turn/river raises = nuts → fold one pair
- They call value light → bet bigger
- They don't bluff rivers → don't hero call

OPEN RAISE (2.5bb)

UTG (14%):
77+, ATs+, KQs, AQo+

MP (18%):
66+, A9s+, A5s-A3s, KJs+, QJs, JTs, AJo+, KQo

CO (30%):
44+, A2s+, K9s+, Q9s+, J9s+, T8s+, 97s+, 86s+, 76s, 65s, ATo+, KJo+, QJo

BTN (45%):
22+, A2s+, K6s+, Q8s+, J8s+, T7s+, 96s+, 85s+, 75s+, 64s+, 54s, A8o+, K9o+, QTo+, JTo

SB (25%):
44+, A2s+, K8s+, Q9s+, J9s+, T8s+, 98s, 87s, A9o+, KTo+ (raise or fold)

VS SINGLE OPEN

3-bet value:
- vs UTG/MP: QQ+, AKs, AKo
- vs CO: JJ+, AQs+, AKo
- vs BTN: TT+, AQs+, AKo

3-bet bluff (vs CO/BTN only):
- A5s-A4s, K9s

Call IP:
- vs UTG/MP: JJ-88, AQs-AJs, KQs
- vs CO: TT-66, AJs-ATs, KQs-KJs, QJs, JTs, T9s
- vs BTN: 99-44, ATs-A9s, KJs-KTs, QJs-QTs, JTs, T9s, 98s, 87s

SB: 3-bet or fold. Never flat.

BB DEFENSE

vs BTN (defend 55%):
- 3-bet: TT+, AQs+, AKo, A5s-A4s
- Call: 99-22, AJs-A2s, KTs+, Q9s+, J9s+, T8s+, 97s+, 86s+, 76s, 65s, A9o+, KJo, QJo
- Fold: K8o-, Q9o-, J9o-, trash offsuit

vs CO (defend 48%):
- 3-bet: QQ+, AKs, AKo
- Call: JJ-55, AQs-A8s, KQs-KTs, QJs-QTs, JTs, T9s, 98s, AJo
- Fold: rest

vs UTG/MP (defend 40%):
- 3-bet: QQ+, AKs, AKo
- Call: JJ-77, AQs-ATs, KQs-KJs, QJs
- Fold: rest

VS 3-BET

4-bet/call: KK+, AKs
Call IP: QQ, JJ, AKo, AQs
Fold: TT-, AJo, KQo, suited connectors, small pairs OOP

VS 4-BET

All-in: KK+
Fold: everything else (QQ, AKo vs tight pool)

POSTFLOP SIZING

Value hands:
- Nuts: 100% pot all streets
- Sets/two pair: 80% pot all streets
- Top pair top kicker: 75%/65%/55%
- Top pair weak kicker: 65% flop, check-call later
- Overpair on ace board: check-call only

Draws:
- Combo draws: 70% pot semi-bluff
- Flush draw: check free, call 40% pot
- Straight draw: check free, call 33% pot

Weak hands: check-fold

FACING AGGRESSION

Flop raise: continue TPTK+
Turn raise: continue two pair+
River raise: continue straights+ (fold if board paired)

AUTO-FOLD

Opens: A6o-A2o, K8o-, Q9o-, J9o- from EP/MP
Facing 3-bet: AJo, ATo, KQo, KJo, TT-22 OOP, suited connectors
Facing turn/river raise: one pair

ADJUSTMENTS

Blinds fold >70%: steal 100% BTN, widen CO
Blinds 3-bet <8%: call 3-bets wider (88, AJs, KQs)
Villain opens >40%: 3-bet wider (AQo, KQs, A3s-A2s)
Villain folds to 3-bet >65%: 3-bet any two from BTN

WIN RATE SOURCES

1. Stealing blinds (40%)
2. Value betting big (35%)
3. Folding to aggression (15%)
4. Not bluffing rivers (10%)
